The paper deals with the problem of compressive phase retrieval, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a variant of the PhaseCode algorithm, which is a method for solving the compressive phase retrieval problem, and discusses its time and memory complexity, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions the use of sparse-graph codes, which are a topic in coding theory and communications, and therefore cs.MM (Multimedia) may also be a relevant sub-category.
